            <h3>Calamba City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Tour the City’s historical sites like Dr. Jose Rizal Shrine and learn more about the country’s national hero.</li>
                <li>2. Swim in any of the hot spring resorts and taste local foods like sinigang na kanduli sa miso, okoy and bulalo for a double treat.</li>
                <li>3. Row your boat from Baywalk to Wonder Island Resort.</li>
                <li>4. Play golf at the famous Canlubang Golf and Country Club and Greenfield Golf and Leisure Club located in Barangays Canlubang and Maunong respectively.</li>
                <li>5. Visit to several garden stalls for different varieties of ornamental plants and to pasalubong centers that sell espasol and buko pie, the City’s most famous pasalubong treats.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Profile</h3>
            <p>Official Name: City of Calamba</p>
            <p>Population: 360,281</p>

            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>The City is 54 kilometers away from Manila. It can be reached via South Luzon Expressway approximately in an hour drive. It serves as the gateway to the provinces of Batangas, Quezon and the Bicol region. The City is serviced by various bus lines 24 hours a day. Modes of transporta- tion include jeepneys and tricycle plying route within the City and to and from nearby municipalities.</p>

